Commentary: fullish length on the stumps, chips this just short of mid-on and they scamper a tight run.

Commentary: overpitched on fifth stump, hammers a straight drive past a vain diving effort at mid-off from Phehlukwayo.
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Haider Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: fullish length drifting onto the pads at 138 kph, tries to whip this through midwicket and is late, clips the pad flap down the leg side and Klaasen dives left to prevent four leg byes.
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Haider Ali, no run

Commentary: back of a length slower ball on fifth stump at 115 kph, plays this with soft hands and an open face behind point.
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: another slower ball telegraphed on a length on fifth stump, Rizwan gets on a knee to keep his hands back and slams a slog over wide long-on.
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Mohammad Rizwan, SIX runs

Commentary: good length ball skids on toward off stump at full pace, goes to flick this leg side but a thick edge falls short of short third man on the ring.
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: full on middle at 96 kph, charges and drives firmly but picks out extra cover on the ring.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: stays in his crease this time to punch a back of a length ball from fourth stump at 92 kph, picks out Smuts again at extra cover but hits it gently enough this time to allow a single.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide, slaps this to cover, but again into a gap to make a single.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Haider Ali, 1 run

Commentary: good length ball on off, cramped for room trying to cut and mishits this into the off side ring.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: short on the stumps trying to flight this more at 84 kph, slams a pull through wide long-on and splits the two leg side boundary riders perfectly.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on the stumps, flicks this along the ground through midwicket.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Rizwan, 2 runs

Commentary: Yikes! You can drive a double-decker through that bat-pad gap! Beautiful flight from Shamsi landing this on a fullish length on fourth stump, the length encourages a drive but it spins sharply back past the bat to clatter into middle stump. Lovely bowling from Shamsi but exposes Haider's technique badly.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Haider Ali, OUT

Commentary: flighted very full at 82 kph on middle, tries to flick through midwicket but comes off the toe into the ground.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: flighted on a good length on fifth stump at 80 kph, prods forward with a full-face defense.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: good length ball pitches on leg stump and spins down the leg side for a wide.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, 1 wide

Commentary: short on the legs again, this time Babar opens up his hips and slams a pull through square leg racing away to the rope.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: flighted full on middle and off, reaches forward to flick this very fine to short fine leg, misfield by Phehlukwayo ensures the run is completed without drama.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: nearly bowled! Shamsi pitches this short on middle and leg, but it skids very very low as Babar goes onto the back foot to hammer another pull through square leg. Instead it shoots under his bat and in between his legs, just whistling past leg stump.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: good length ball on fourth stump, pokes at this with hard hands and it floats short of extra cover.
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: another good length ball on fifth stump punched uppishly just wide of extra cover to long-off.
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: flighted on sixth stump on a fullish length, sweeps this very hard in front of square and splits the boundary riders again to the rope.
Commentary_short: Smuts to Mohammad Rizwan, FOUR runs

Commentary: good length ball on off, nudged with soft hands into the ring for a single.
Commentary_short: Smuts to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: fuller on off, punched straight down the ground to long-off.
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full on off, defended into the off side.
Commentary_short: Smuts to Mohammad Rizwan, no run

Commentary: short on the stumps, pulls this flat through midwicket for a single.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: dropped! Thin edge, very difficult to hold onto for Klaasen. really unfair to call that a drop actually. Short outside off, goes to cut, thin bottom edge goes off the knees into short fine leg. Never touched the gloves.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Mohammad Rizwan, 1 run

Commentary: short and spins down leg, comes off the pads so no wide.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: flighted full on off stump, strikes clean through the line lofting this straight down the ground for maximum value.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, SIX runs

Commentary: good length ball outside off, guides this with an open face through third man for a long single, they think about coming back for two before settling.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: oh dear. For as good as Rizwan has been this series, that was a positively dreadful sweep shot, and now an even worse decision to ask for a review. As plumb as it gets. It was a very full delivery on middle, practically a full toss as he tries to sweep a yorker length ball pitched too full for the sweep shot from Shamsi. He plays late and over the top of this, struck on the bottom of the pad just above the boot tongue in front of middle stump. Ball-tracking shows it was ripping out leg stump with a full red. Pakistan lose a review.
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Mohammad Rizwan, OUT
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Rizwan lbw b Shamsi 42 (41m 30b 5x4 2x6) SR: 140.00

Commentary: short and wide, slaps this to extra cover.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: fuller and flatter at 96 kph on middle stump, flicks this to midwicket.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: darts this flat down the leg side. Wide called.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Hussain Talat, 1 wide

Commentary: charges Fortuin and is fortunate this lands in no man's land! Bowled flat on middle on a good length, beaten in flight trying to flick over midwicket, it goes straight instead of turning in to his body, a leading edge is skied over mid-off but the man coming in off the rope can't get there in time.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: good length on the stumps, tapped through the ring and played gently enough to come back for two.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: good length ball slapped back toward the non-striker, eludes Fortuin to go for a single.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: short on the stumps, slapped through mid-on for another single.
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: lots of width outside off, might have been a wide if he'd left it, instead it's a chop to third man for a single
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Hussain Talat, 1 run

Commentary: dipping on the toes, whipped to midwicket and just another single
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full face of the bat, punched back through the line of the ball as Shamsi pounces in his followthrough
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Hussain Talat, no run

Commentary: back of a length, whipped to midwicket, with just enough lack of pace to rush back for the second. Expert placement
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Hussain Talat, 2 runs

Commentary: too full, too straight, too tricksy off the pitch, and Talat has wafted all around it! Played for the spin, this one zipped through, walloping the off stump and leaving a bigger dent in Pakistan's chase. It might be Babar or bust at this rate ...
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Hussain Talat, OUT

Commentary: solid block on a full length, the end of a taxing over
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Asif Ali, no run

Commentary: back of a length, a languid biff to midwicket, one the back foot with the short-arm pull
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: opens the face on the fuller length, fenced into the gap at third man and a fine tumbling stop intercepts the boundary
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: short and wide, and clobbered through point! Regal from Babar, standing tall, unleashing the forearms, and carved to the rope!
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: too short again, this is loose from Sipamla, banged into the deck and sitting up outside off, Babar is anchored on the back foot, rifling his wristy pull through wide long-on!
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: tighter line, on the back foot, an open-faced press to point. Babar keeps the strike, and keeps Pakistan on course
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: very full, angled into the leg side, and another single to the cause
Commentary_short: Sipamla to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: round the wicket, looped onto a middle-and-off line, and pressed with a full face to mid-off
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: sharp turn on a full length, back and across to poke out to cover
Commentary_short: Smuts to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: flicked with intent off the full length again, grabbed in the followthrough
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: whipped to the on-side, looking for the single again
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: tight wicket-to-wicket line, just back of a length and holding up in the turf. Cautious prod to defend the timbers
Commentary_short: Smuts to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: shorter, and this time Babar can free his arms with a whip to leg, but the sweeper limits the damage. That's a very useful over to tighten the requirement. The hundred is up, South Africa were 93 for 7 at this stage, but Miller was only getting started...
Commentary_short: Smuts to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: clattered through backward point! Pretorius's first ball back skids into another wafty cut, and immediately he's under pressure
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: Babar's on the march now! Too much width again, just back of a length, a flog on the up, through third man for back-to-back fours
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: tighter line, nudged to the leg side
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Babar Azam, 1 run

Commentary: full face of the bat, punched to long-off, better length from Pretorius
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: too short once more, Babar doesn't quite time his pull but with long-on set deep, he seizes his chance to sprint back for two
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Babar Azam, 2 runs

Commentary: bowled him! Perfection from Pretorius, so full and crucially it tails in late, cramping Babar as he plays across the line and finds the ball is always ahead of his bat! A priceless strike at a crucial juncture. A decent return to form for Babar, but has he left too much for his team-mates?
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Babar Azam, OUT

Commentary: shaping down the leg side, a free run to the cause
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Asif Ali, 1 wide

Commentary: outside off, grips and turns back into the right-hander, who rocks back to flick to leg
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Asif Ali, 1 run

Commentary: pushed into the off-side, head over the ball in watchful fashion
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: on the back foot, flicked to the on-side, and another well-judged two runs to keep chipping away
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Asif Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: slotted straight to Miller at long-on! Four for Shamsi, and that was like lollipop-stealing! Tossed up, dipping on the toes, confounding an ambitious tonk through the line, never got proper hold of the shot, and a non-starter of an innings has ended...
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Asif Ali, OUT
Dismissal_text: Asif Ali c Miller b Shamsi 7 (21m 8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 87.50

Commentary: another wrong'un, patted back down the pitch
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: outside edge, a bit of bite on a full length, squeezed to the off-side and that's the end of an outstanding and potentially game-seizing spell...
Commentary_short: Shamsi to Faheem Ashraf, no run

Commentary: wide line from round the wicket, eludes a flat-footed drive, a useful dot to ease into his over
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: another waft at a back-of-a-length wide ball, a fumble from the keeper denies another dot
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 bye

Commentary: slower ball, piled through the line, and clears the leg of long-on! Phehlukwayo over-thought that one, ended up dobbing it into the slot, and once the pace was picked, that was curtains!
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Faheem Ashraf, SIX runs

Commentary: wide and full, he reverts to that outside-off approach and claws his over back with another priceless dot
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Faheem Ashraf, no run

Commentary: huge wipe, high into the night sky ... who wants it? No-one, it lands safe in the covers, but wait ... this looks like a run-out! A bit of ball-watching all round ... but no, the return to the keeper is fractionally too late from Klaasen. Gosh. And breathe!
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Faheem Ashraf, 2 runs

Commentary: too wide, outside the tramlines as Faheem cocks his wrists and lets it go
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Faheem Ashraf, 1 wide

Commentary: decent finish, shape back into the left-hander on a full length, snicks the inside edge, on the bounce through to the keeper. Lots of dots means only ten from the over, despite that six
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Faheem Ashraf, no run

Commentary: scuffed out to backward point off a full length from round the wicket
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: shaped across the leftie, ends up as a very wide full-toss outside off, but Faheem is already committed to a paddle sweep, deflecting the ball behind square
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Faheem Ashraf, 1 run

Commentary: well bowled, a fraction straighter, but outside off in the end, an inside-edged drive with flat feet goes nowhere
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: pongo-ed towards the tea-party at long-on! Too full, straight line, Nawaz decides this one must travel, and it does!
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Nawaz, SIX runs

Commentary: shuffling at the crease, opening the face on a full length, poked out to backward point
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: slogged straight to long-on! Fortuin snags a priceless wicket with the final ball of his spell, sliding across the left-hander, forcing him to over-reach in his bid for a power-hit, and he can't connect properly! Straight down the throat, as this chase see-saws once more!
Commentary_short: Fortuin to Faheem Ashraf, OUT
Dismissal_text: Faheem Ashraf c Miller b Fortuin 10 (20m 8b 0x4 1x6) SR: 125.00

Commentary: wide of off stump, and eludes a helicopter wipe of the wrists
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Hasan Ali, no run

Commentary: exceptional bowling! Oh, that's harsh! No stroke offered as Pretorius finds the perfect tram-line cutter, but it's called wide
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Hasan Ali, 1 wide

Commentary: cracked out to deep point, again aiming wide, forcing the batsman to reach for it, and he does so effectively enough
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Hasan Ali, 2 runs

Commentary: slower ball, and battered through the line towards long-on, gathered on the bounce and it's just another single. Hasan had rather higher ambitions for that one
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Hasan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: flashed through third man, and there's one of those boundaries! Cleverly played, aimed for yorker, but there's just enough width outside off to open the face and use the pace
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Mohammad Nawaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: tremendous bowling, a slower ball on a wide line, left alone by Nawaz who is fishing for the wide but doesn't get it this time
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Mohammad Nawaz, no run

Commentary: flogged behind point for a hugely important four! Hits the deck hard and sits up, Nawaz had to wait and wait to time his stroke, and he did so brilliantly, placing it just to the right of the cover sweeper!
Commentary_short: Pretorius to Mohammad Nawaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: shocker! a waist-high no-ball, hoisted over square leg, and there goes the game! It's a no-ball, a free hit ... everything but the chassis itself has come off for South Africa
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Hasan Ali, (no ball) SIX runs

Commentary: slips in a decent delivery in the circumstances, full and straight and dug out back to the bowler. But it's just the last rites from here...
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Hasan Ali, 1 run

Commentary: oh lordie, that's horrific! The wet ball slips out of his fingers, and barely hits the cut strip on any dimension
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 wide

Commentary: crunched on the up to deep point, Pretorius cuts off the four...
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Mohammad Nawaz, 1 run

Commentary: full length, and a slashed edge over the covers, skims off the dew and over the rope. Pakistan believe now!
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Hasan Ali, FOUR runs

Commentary: waist-high full toss, wasted into the stands! Hasan finishes in style, with a booming pull over midwicket, and Pakistan have held their nerve in a gripping decider!
Commentary_short: Phehlukwayo to Hasan Ali, SIX runs
